node.title: Authorities think they've identified "Little Miss Nobody" 62 years later
node.description: They exhumed her body to get DNA. Her burned, partially buried remains were found in a remote desert area of north-central Arizona. They thought she was between 3 and 6 years old.
node.content: ["Prescott, Arizona\u00a0\u2014 Authorities in north-central Arizona believe they now know the name of a little girl whose burned remains were found in a remote desert area 62 years ago.", "Yavapai County sheriff's officials are planning to give a full update and overview of the investigation Tuesday at Yavapai Community College in Prescott. ", "Dubbed \"Little Miss Nobody,\" the girl's partially buried remains were located in a wash on July 31, 1960.  ", "Investigators believed the girl was between 3 and 6 years old and her remains were buried about a week or two before being discovered. ", "Authorities say there were no obvious injuries to her decomposed body and the case was ruled a homicide. ", "The Prescott community raised money to provide a funeral for the unidentified child in 1960. ", "In 2018, her remains were exhumed so DNA samples could be taken. ", "The sheriff's office and a Texas DNA company raised $4,000 earlier this year to fund specialized testing and finally identify the girl."]
